rlQcnMib.name: rlQcnMib
rlQcnMib.description: Added: rlQcnFeatureStatus rlQcnPriorityStateTable rlQcnIfStateTable rlQcnCmnPriority rlQcnCpPfcSetPoint rlQcnCpNonPfcSetPoint rlQcnCpFeedbackWeight rlQcnCpMinSampleBase.

rlQcnFeatureStatus.name: rlQcnFeatureStatus
rlQcnFeatureStatus.description: This scalar indicates QCN enable status.

rlQcnPriorityStateTable.name: rlQcnPriorityStateTable
rlQcnPriorityStateTable.description: This table describes Quantized Congestion Notification per Priority state.

rlQcnPriorityStateEntry.name: rlQcnPriorityStateEntry
rlQcnPriorityStateEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes priority state. The index is represented by rlQcnPriorityStatePriority.

rlQcnPriorityAdminStateReason.name: rlQcnPriorityAdminStateReason
rlQcnPriorityAdminStateReason.description: Reason for admin status (if admin status not equal to oper).

rlQcnPriorityStateStatus.name: rlQcnPriorityStateStatus
rlQcnPriorityStateStatus.description: The status of a table entry. It is used to delete/Add an entry from/to this table.

rlQcnIfStateTable.name: rlQcnIfStateTable
rlQcnIfStateTable.description: This table describes Quantized Congestion Notification per interface state.

rlQcnIfStateEntry.name: rlQcnIfStateEntry
rlQcnIfStateEntry.description: Each entry in this table describes state of the interface. The index is represented by rlQcnIfStateIfIndex.

rlQcnIfStateCpCreationEn.name: rlQcnIfStateCpCreationEn
rlQcnIfStateCpCreationEn.description: Congestion point creation enable status. If CP creation is enabled for an interface, the system automatically creates a Congestion Point (CP) for a queue of that interface if at least one QCN priority (Oper state) is mapped to that queue.

rlQcnIfStateStatus.name: rlQcnIfStateStatus
rlQcnIfStateStatus.description: The status of a table entry. It is used to delete/Add an entry from/to this table.

rlQcnCmnPriority.name: rlQcnCmnPriority
rlQcnCmnPriority.description: This scalar indicates priority which is used for all Congestion Notification Messages (CNMs) transmitted by the device.

rlQcnCpPfcSetPoint.name: rlQcnCpPfcSetPoint
rlQcnCpPfcSetPoint.description: This scalar indicates QCN set-point of an egress queue on PFC enabled interface. Value of set-point is in bytes and in multiples of 512.

rlQcnCpNonPfcSetPoint.name: rlQcnCpNonPfcSetPoint
rlQcnCpNonPfcSetPoint.description: This scalar indicates QCN set-point of an egress queue on PFC disabled interface. Value of set-point is in bytes and in multiples of 512.

rlQcnCpFeedbackWeight.name: rlQcnCpFeedbackWeight
rlQcnCpFeedbackWeight.description: This scalar indicates Feedback Weight of a QCN egress queue. The weight is equal to two to the power of this object. Thus, if this number contains a -1, weight = 1/2.

rlQcnCpMinSampleBase.name: rlQcnCpMinSampleBase
rlQcnCpMinSampleBase.description: This scalar indicates minimum number of bytes to enqueue in a QCN egress queue between transmissions of Congestion Notification Messages. Value of min-sample-base is in bytes and in multiples of 16.

rlQcnCpSetPoint.name: rlQcnCpSetPoint
rlQcnCpSetPoint.description: This scalar indicates QCN set-point of an egress queue. Value of set-point is in bytes and in multiples of 512.
